A three-month-old baby found dead at the weekend has been named by police.
Abel Stewart MacDonald died in a house in Culloden, Inverness, on Saturday.
Emergency services were called to a property at about 12.55pm and found the young boy dead at the scene.
Officers are investigating the circumstances but it is not thought to be suspicious.
A report on the death will be sent to the procurator fiscal.
